    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-12-19T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-12-19T12:00:00-05:00" n="198"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d198">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">835.24/12–1947: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Belgium</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Millard</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Brussels</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-12-19T18:00:00+01:00"
                            >December 19, 1947—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2014. <gloss target="#t_reDeptel1">Redeptel</gloss> 1758<note n="29"
                        xml:id="d198fn1">Not printed.</note> and <gloss target="#t_Embtel1"
                        >Embtel</gloss> 1937, December 9. <gloss target="#t_Embdesp1"
                        >Embdesp</gloss> 1689, December 11,<note n="29" xml:id="d198fn2">Not
                        printed.</note> forwards detailed information from ConsGen Antwerp
                    indicating 583 tanks and 797 jeeps and trucks shipped Antwerp to Argentina from
                    March 5 until November 17, 1947. Have received today <gloss target="#t_FonOff1"
                        >FonOff</gloss> note from De Gruben indicating 361 tanks left Antwerp
                    between June 24 and November 17. These shipments occurred during period when
                    arms transit shipment required license (see <gloss target="#t_Embdesp1"
                        >Embdesp</gloss> 1283, May 29<note n="29" xml:id="d198fn3">Not
                        printed.</note>) <gloss target="#t_FonOff1">FonOff</gloss> adds <hi
                        rend="italic">Rio Diamante</hi> and <hi rend="italic">Rio Secundo</hi>
                    schedule load 90 tanks each toward mid-January but license refused. States Lloyd
                    register announced arrival all vessels La Plata. <gloss target="#t_FonOff1"
                        >FonOff</gloss>, therefore, feels tanks not rerouted.</p>
                <p>Embassy official last evening saw official Ministry Food and Exportation who
                    stated categorically reports shipment tanks Russia completely unfounded (<gloss
                        target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 1919, December 6<note n="29"
                        xml:id="d198fn4">Not printed.</note>). Extensive inquiries Brussels and
                    Antwerp have revealed nothing collaborating [<hi rend="italic"
                        >corroborating?</hi>] <hi rend="italic">Daily Express</hi> story which I
                    consider groundless. Brussels daily <hi rend="italic">Soir</hi> yesterday and
                    today carries factual obviously inspired article of tanks shipments Argentina in
                    refutation story their shipment <gloss target="#t_USSR1">USSR</gloss> which many
                    papers have reprinted. Airmail despatch follows.<note n="29" xml:id="d198fn5"
                        >Not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Sent Department, repeated Buenos Aires unnumbered.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Millard</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
